overview: The user wanted to enhance the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire application. The assistant began by analyzing the existing
  design, identifying areas like the generic color palette, plain backgrounds,
  and basic form elements as needing improvement. A new sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced, and all core UI components (cards, checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, progress bars) were restyled. The main questionnaire form
  layout, intro section, and all subsequent content sections were updated to
  reflect the new aesthetic, featuring subtle gradients, improved typography,
  and consistent card-style groupings. During the process, a console error
  related to  values being passed to input components was identified and
  fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle such values. The
  changes were verified through linting and browser checks, resulting in a more
  polished, cohesive, and professional-looking application.
